# Environment Configuration for quran-api
# 
# This file documents environment variables used across different contexts:
# 1. Local Development (copy this file to .env for local use)
# 2. GitHub Actions (configured as Secrets/Variables in repository settings)
# 3. Production Cloudflare Workers (configured in wrangler.toml or Cloudflare dashboard)

# ==============================================================================
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (Cloudflare Workers local mode)
# ==============================================================================
# Copy this file to .env and update values for local development
# Run: wrangler dev

# Cloudflare Account (for local deployment)
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=your_api_token_here
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=your_account_id_here

# JWT Configuration (development - use weak secret for local only)
JWT_SECRET=dev-secret-change-in-production-do-not-commit

# Environment
ENVIRONMENT=development

# ==============================================================================
# GITHUB ACTIONS DEPLOYMENT
# ==============================================================================
# These are configured in GitHub repository settings:
# Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
#
# SECRETS (encrypted, not visible in logs):
#   CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN     - Cloudflare API token with Workers/Pages edit permissions
#   CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID    - Your Cloudflare account ID
#
# VARIABLES (visible, reusable configuration):
#   NODE_VERSION             - Node.js version (default: 20)
#   ENVIRONMENT             - Deployment environment (default: production)
#
# To add these in GitHub:
# 1. Go to repository Settings
# 2. Secrets and variables → Actions
# 3. Add secrets/variables as shown above
# 4. See: docs/GITHUB_VARIABLES_SETUP.md for detailed guide

# ==============================================================================
# PRODUCTION (Cloudflare Workers)
# ==============================================================================
# Production configuration is managed in Cloudflare Dashboard, NOT in wrangler.toml
#
# wrangler.toml stays with placeholders for local development:
# - database_id = "ignored-locally"
# - id = "ignored-locally" (for KV)
#
# Configure production bindings in Cloudflare Dashboard:
# Workers & Pages → quran-api → Settings → Bindings
#
# Add D1 binding:
#   Variable name: DB
#   D1 database: quran-db (select from dropdown)
#
# Add KV binding:
#   Variable name: CACHE
#   KV namespace: quran-cache (select from dropdown)
#
# Configure production secrets in Cloudflare Dashboard:
# Workers & Pages → quran-api → Settings → Variables and Secrets
#
# Add environment variable:
#   ENVIRONMENT = production
#
# Add secret:
#   JWT_SECRET = [your-production-secret]  # Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
#
# This approach (from quran-th):
# ✅ No placeholder replacement needed
# ✅ Production secrets never touch Git
# ✅ Same wrangler.toml works for local and production
# ✅ Wrangler uses dashboard bindings automatically

# ==============================================================================
# DATABASE CONFIGURATION
# ==============================================================================
# Local development uses local D1 (automatic with "ignored-locally" placeholder)
# Run migrations locally: wrangler d1 migrations apply DB --local
# Run migrations in production: wrangler d1 migrations apply DB --remote

# ==============================================================================
# KV NAMESPACE
# ==============================================================================
# Local development uses local KV (automatic with "ignored-locally" placeholder)
# Production KV is configured via Cloudflare Dashboard bindings (see above)

# ==============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: EXTERNAL DATABASES
# ==============================================================================
# Only if using external databases (not D1):
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host/database

# ==============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ==============================================================================
# NEVER commit actual secrets or production values to .env or .env.example!
# - Use different secrets for local/staging/production
# - Rotate secrets periodically (recommended: every 90 days)
# - Never share .env files or production secrets
# - Add .env to .gitignore (already done)

# For setup instructions, see:
# - docs/CLOUDFLARE_DEPLOYMENT_SETUP.md
# - docs/GITHUB_VARIABLES_SETUP.md
# - docs/GITHUB_CONFIG_QUICKREF.md
